\
## Failure Modes & Safeguards\
\
- **Rubber-Sheet Tear** (massive reproject breaks edges)  \
  \uc0\u8594  Safeguard: bounded moves per tick; queue large moves as staged weaves.\
\
- **Topology Drift** (weights and geometry diverge)  \
  \uc0\u8594  Safeguard: periodic coherence checks; enforce prune/weave caps.\
\
- **Over-Fusion / Over-Fission** (loss of diversity or fragmentation)  \
  \uc0\u8594  Safeguard: SHI diversity term; minimum/maximum cluster sizes.\
\
- **Pigment Flooding** (one hue dominates space)  \
  \uc0\u8594  Safeguard: saturation clamps; SHI pigment balance watch.\
\
- **Residue Pooling at Surface** (choking with soot)  \
  \uc0\u8594  Safeguard: Purification pass + Sink transforms prioritized.\
\
